@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Delivery — Sequence Diagram

queue "Kafka / Event Bus" as Kafka
participant "notification-service" as Notification
participant "identity/preferences" as Preferences
participant "template/i18n" as Template
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "FCM / APNs" as Push
participant "SMTP / Netgsm" as EmailSms
participant "Client" as Client

Kafka -> Notification : DomainEvent
Notification -> DB : dedup check
Notification -> Preferences : load preferences/devices
Preferences --> Notification : prefs + device tokens
Notification -> Template : render localized content
Template --> Notification : title/body/deeplink
Notification -> DB : create Notification + Attempts
Notification -> Push : send push
Push --> Notification : delivery result
Notification -> EmailSms : send email/SMS if selected
EmailSms --> Notification : delivery result
Notification -> DB : update final/attempt state
Notification -> Kafka : NotificationSent/Failed
Notification -> Client : in-app inbox sync / badge count

note bottom
Notification service consumes domain events and owns inbox + channel attempts.
Domain services do not call push/SMS/email providers directly.
end note
@enduml
